reviews.text:
My family and I used to love this place, everyone could find something they liked. We were 2-3x a month diners.
However, the last time we got boneless chicken wings the meat was rotten. It had smelled like something gross when we first walked in, now I realize it was rotten chicken smell and we should have left right then. Waitress was very apologetic. The waitresses and service has always been top noch here and it's not her fault.
It doesn't matter what the sell by date is, if the chicken smells rotten....... It IS rotten and just throw it away.
Sadly, we will never be back.
We love this place.  The sauce is so good.  Food is always hot and fresh.  Love the beer.

Food was gross. Waitress was not attentive at all and the atmosphere smelt like beef. The chicken nuggets from McDonalds have more seasoning. Took and hour to get our food just for it to taste like rubber do not go here

Mistie was awesome and the food was delicious!! Seemed busy and a little understaffed, but overall not bad. 5 stars because of our waitress Mistie. She was very apologetic about the wait and sincerely cared about our experience. We will be back.
Love this place the service is quick. I love their wings very juicy and tender. Don't know how the cook does it but it's wonderful and it's a very nice relaxing place to eat.

editorial_summary.overview: Sports bar specializing in beer & baked chicken wings topped with various signature sauces.

detailedReviews.text:
I went to this establishment this past Thursday, and this review could be an east coast guy struggling with Utah food/ and lack of awareness that Utah has:

1. Wings were decent- lemon pepper has no butter, or lemon juice to soak thru the skin of the wing and get to the chicken. So it is just lemon pepper and salt on the outside of the chicken.

2. Lack of and medium, or mold sauce was weird. They only have a hot sauce that was decent, but no mild or medium was weird and frankly weird

3. Thursday night: music on- football was on ravens vs bengals. Please put that audio on- or the Utah hockey club was on could have put that audio also on.

4. The server we had I forgot her name because she only took our food and handed us the bill. Never once checked on us, refilled a drink, nor ask us how we liked our burnt chips.

Overall this is the 3-4 time I have been here and I always always want to love this place but the food isn‚Äôt good, service sucks, and I will long for a sports place in Utah

detailedReviews.author: Aaron
detailedReviews.text:
I told my friends "I want to be disappointed and frustrated tonight: I'm going to wing nutz!" In perfect fashion, when I got in they said one oven was broken so the food will take longer, and 45 minutes later I received my overcooked, dry, incorrect order.

I have a long-standing and irreplaceable abusive relationship with this chain.  I've been going to Wing Nutz for over a decade, sometimes for two meals a day! The wait for your food, at any location, any time of day is between 15 and 150 minutes. Throw a dart. The quality is also completely random. My "home" location had one manager that got drunk and danced like a stripper on the bar. Then another manager tried (almost successfully!) to sleep with my girlfriend.

So why the 5-star review, you might ask!? Quite simply, this chain is my favorite train wreck to watch, and I want it to stay around as long as possible. It's continued existence already defies all logic and hopefully this review contributes to that end.

Cheers! :)

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Spain
detailedReviews.text:
This place is close to my house and once in awhile my spouse and I want to watch a game and have some wings and beer. We have been going to Wing Nutz for almost 15 years and it has been going downhill pretty steadily since 2020.

The last several times we‚Äôve been in, they‚Äôve been shortstaffed. The food has been decent to great, but the wait for food and a check was ridiculous. They discontinued some of our favorite sauces, and we haven‚Äôt been in probably 7-8 months.

We decided to give them another try, and it was a bad decision. It appeared that there was some kind of staff/family party going on. The kitchen and waitstaff were eating and drinking at the tables and then getting up and going into the kitchen and wandering behind the bar. Our waitress got our order wrong, we had to flag the staff repeatedly to get water and the check.

The tip of the iceberg was the domestic dispute that was taking place between what (I assume) were friends of the owner. The male was very loud and obviously under the influence with a bunch of small children at the table. His partner, also obviously under the influence, was wearing a swimsuit, a t-shirt, sunglasses, and nothing else (I mean, get it girl). They were having a wild time at the bar while everyone else was in a restaurant.

At some point the male got in their SUV with the two of them shouting at one another, she had the sense to get the children out of the car, and he sped off. Super cool of the owner/manager to let his friend drive off drunk/high whatever leaving his partner and kids behind. Owner/manager did spend about 30 minutes talking to her on the patio while one of the kids was sobbing in the restaurant and a kind adult friend was checking on her. And you know, no one manning the kitchen and the waitresses swapping stories instead of waiting on tables. Owner/manager also appeared to be drunk and/or extremely high. No big deal.

It appears (also based on recent comments) that the manager/owner doesn‚Äôt really care about anything except having parties with his friends. Will not be coming back. Am also hoping those kids make it home safe.

customerMoodAnalysis.sentimentSummary: Customer opinions are divided. The 3.3/5 rating from 100 recent reviews suggests some great experiences mixed with areas needing attention.

strengthsPerceived: Customers consistently praise the staff, especially waitresses like Mistie, for their exceptional service and care, making them feel valued and well-attended. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The wings are described as "out of this world," with specific mentions of the cook's expertise in preparing them perfectly. - SEO services can leverage this for better visibility
The food is consistently described as hot, fresh, and delicious, with specific mentions of the sauce and beer. - review management can highlight this positive aspect
improvementOpportunities: Negative reviews and reputation issues due to poor food quality and service - review management can address this concern
Lack of atmosphere/ambiance awareness, including issues with cleanliness and maintenance - social media marketing can improve this area

neutral.text: Great food if they can get the order right. Second time in a row I got boneless wings instead of bone in like I asked. Their boneless wings aren't great that's why I don't get them. The phone also never works so I can't call and say hey can you make my order correct, nope gotta drive back up there.

negative.author: Cindy Hatch
negative.text:
My family and I used to love this place, everyone could find something they liked. We were 2-3x a month diners.
However, the last time we got boneless chicken wings the meat was rotten. It had smelled like something gross when we first walked in, now I realize it was rotten chicken smell and we should have left right then. Waitress was very apologetic. The waitresses and service has always been top noch here and it's not her fault.
It doesn't matter what the sell by date is, if the chicken smells rotten....... It IS rotten and just throw it away.
Sadly, we will never be back.

negative.text: Terrible service and grilled wings only! Gross
